		<title>03SKILL CENTRE</title>
		<content>                                       
                                       
    SKILL CENTRE                       
   The Skill Centre lies to the        
 north of Townhill. The centre was     
 projected in 1963 after the NCB mine  
 previously on the site was closed.The 
 centre was opened in 1965 after       
 extensive work took place.            
   The centre can cater for about 100  
 trainees including those on day       
 release from interested firms.These   
 trainees come for about 10 weeks to a 
 year to complete their course.The     
 centre teaches:-                      
 Bricklaying,Joinery,Welding,          
 Agricultural Engineering,Forging and  
 Industrial Fitting.                   
                                       
                                       
                                       
